-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- pokemon_rb.lua — game module for the Archipelago BizHawk connector.
--                  Pokémon Red & Blue (Game Boy)
--
-- STATUS: location DETECTION + goal are REAL and SOURCE-DERIVED from the official
-- AP world worlds/pokemon_rb (client.py + locations.py + rom.py, main branch). The
-- 709-entry location table was GENERATED by executing the real locations.py and
-- replicating client.py's exact location_map / location_bytes_bits build (NOT
-- hand-copied), so the ap_id → flag mapping is byte-for-byte what the official
-- client uses. Loads crash-free on any cartridge; self-disables on a non-Pokémon
-- ROM (validates the GB header game title, exactly like client.validate_rom).
--
-- MEMORY MODEL (BizHawk GB domains)
-- ──────────────────────────────────
--   The PokemonRBClient (a BizHawkClient) reads work RAM ("WRAM") for all flag
--   arrays and reads the cartridge header ("ROM") only to identify the game.
--   client.py DATA_LOCATIONS (all WRAM unless noted):
--     EventFlag      0x1735, len 0x140    Missable   0x161A, len 0x20
--     Hidden         0x16DE, len 0x0E     Rod        0x1716, len 0x01
--     DexSanityFlag  0x1A71, len 19       GameStatus 0x1A84, len 1
--     ResetCheck     0x0100, len 4        CrashCheck1 0x1731,len 2
--     CrashCheck2    0x1617, len 1        CrashCheck3 0x1A70, len 1
--     CrashCheck4    0x16DD, len 1
--   A location is "checked" when  data[array][byte] & (1 << bit)  is set, where
--   (array, byte, bit) come from the location's flag (byte=flag//8, bit=flag%8;
--   Rod uses byte=0, bit=flag). Two "list" locations need BOTH an EventFlag bit
--   AND a Missable bit set (client.py "list" branch).
--
-- ROM IDENTITY (client.validate_rom): the GB header game title at ROM 0x134 (12
--   bytes) is "POKEMON RED\0" or "POKEMON BLUE". There is no separate AP magic —
--   the patched ROM keeps the original title; the seed name lives at ROM 0xFFDB.
--   We mirror validate_rom: accept either title, otherwise stay idle.
--
-- GOAL (client.py VICTORY): EventFlag byte 280 bit 0 (the Hall-of-Fame event) —
--   `data["EventFlag"][280] & 1`. No check location uses that flag.
--
-- WHAT THIS DOES (mirrors worlds/pokemon_rb/client.py game_watcher)
--   • poll(): read the five flag arrays → AP location ids, gated to the slot's
--     server location set AND to the in-game / not-crashed gate (GameStatus is
--     0x2A or 0xAC, ResetCheck ≠ 0x7FFFFFFF, the four CrashCheck guards) so the
--     title screen / a corrupted frame never reports checks. This is the exact
--     gate client.game_watcher uses before it collects locations.
--   • is_goal_complete(): EventFlag[280] & 1 (the default + only goal).
--   • receive_item(): NO-OP (documented). items_handling = 0b001 — the server
--     sends only THIS slot's own items, and the PATCHED GAME grants its locally
--     found items itself, so a SOLO seed plays fully and every check is reported
--     in a multiworld. Delivering REMOTE items is the client's APItem-byte
--     handshake (write the next item's code to WRAM 0x00FF only while the game
--     has cleared it to 0, tracking the save's own ItemIndex at 0x1A6E); that is
--     a guarded WRAM WRITE that must be confirmed in-emulator before shipping, so
--     it is intentionally left out rather than risk mis-applying an item. The
--     pipe bridge still delivers items launcher-side for games that implement it;
--     here it is the one deferred piece (same posture as cvcotm.lua).
--
-- MODULE CONTRACT (called by bizhawk_ap_connector.lua)
--   M.init(ctx) / M.poll() -> {ids} / M.is_goal_complete() -> bool /
--   M.receive_item(item_id, meta)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

local M = {}
M.name = "pokemon_rb"

